  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" Samiullah versus The State of Bihar & Ors. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_11_448_474','2025INSC1292'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SAMIULLAH<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE STATE OF BIHAR & ORS. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 11 S.C.R. 448</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1292</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010005932025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : PAMIDIGHANTAM SRI NARASIMHA, JOYMALYA BAGCHI</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Issue arose as regard the sub-rules (xvii) and (xviii) to r.19 of the Bihar Registration Rules, 2008 empowering registering authorities to refuse registration of documents, if proof of mutation of the property under sale in favour of the vendor not produced along with if ultra vires the Act. Headnotes&dagger; Bihar Registration Rules, 2008 &ndash; r.19 (xvii) and (xviii) &ndash; Refusal of duly presented document &ndash; Sub-rules (xvii) and (xviii) introduced by way of amendments to r.19 empowering registering authorities to refuse registration of documents,<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 07-11-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 13429/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_11_448_474','2025INSC1292','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_1